I read this last night and didn't really like it enough to upvote, but I think I've now changed my mind. I only really have two substantial criticisms; first, the whole SPC thing. It's not explicitly mentioned in the article, only here in the discussion, so that's not too bad, but it still irks me. I think this would be a lot more interesting if it were just some vessel of inexplicable origin, instead of having a clear purpose. Secondly, and this is more superficial, the containment procedures are really short. I mean, bulking them out any further would just be padding for the sake of padding, but it still seems like too little. Maybe add a bit about cleaning procedures? Overall, though, I like this, so +1.







